An Ikeja Magistrates’ Court yesterday remanded a 25- year-old man, Usman Ahmed, at the Kirikiri Prisons for allegedly raping an 18-year-old girl (name withheld). Ahmed was arraigned before Magistrate Bola Osunsanmi on a lone charge of rape. The magistrate did not take his plea but ordered that Ahmed be kept in Kirikiri Prison custody pending advice from the Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP). Prosecuting Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP) Ezekiel Ayorinde told the court that the defendant committed the crime at his residence in Ijora. Ayorinde alleged that Ahmed raped the girl at his residence and penetrated her private part several times. He said the defendant forcefully took the girl away from her parents without their consent, and held her captive for many days in his house and started having canal knowledge of his victim unlawfully. He added that the parents of the girl searched for the girl until the fourth day when they were informed that she was with the defendant. He said the parents of the girl, based on the information given to them, later traced their daughter to the house of Ahmed in Ijora. Thereafter, they reported the matter to the police, who arrested the defendant. Osunsanmi adjourned the matter till August  6.